        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:59PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 158 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northwest of Tuscarora, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rainfall and gusty winds that could knock down tree
limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage
to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wilson Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
